{"id": "62b0702f-26e9-4914-b27f-deb555f998f8", "title": "India's blueprint falls in place: The key takeaways from New Zealand series", "url": "https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/sports/cricket/icc-mens-t20-world-cup/indias-blueprint-falls-in-place-the-key-takeaways-from-new-zealand-series/articleshow/127923933.cms", "category": "sports", "source": "Times of India", "published_at": "2026-02-05T10:25:12+05:30", "full_text": "Surya Kumar Yadav (PTI Photo)

Dear Gautam Gambhir and Suryakumar Yadav, don't let Ishan Kishan down

A dominant series win against New Zealand offered India more than just momentum, it brought clarity. Suryakumar Yadav rediscovered his touch, Ishan Kishan and Shivam Dube forced their way into the conversation with explosive returns, Rinku Singh underlined his growing allround value and the bowling blueprint fell into place. ..SURYA’S TIMELY RETURN TO FORM: A 4–1 series win capped a satisfying T20I outing against New Zealand for India captain Suryakumar Yadav. “There’s no difference between the Surya of 2025 and now — I was just out of runs then,” he said. Leading the run charts with 242, Surya stood out less for the numbers than for his clarity: secure in his method and buoyed by the team’s momentum.ISHAN TEES OFF: Frozen out before the series, Kishan forced his way back with three explosive knocks — 76 off 32, 28 off 13 and a blistering 103 off 43 — firmly announcing his World Cup intent. By the end of the series, he had reclaimed the wicketkeeping gloves, pushing Sanju Samson to the fringes.DUBE FLEXES ALLROUND MUSCLE: Dube added power and balance, striking 36 off 18 and 65 off 23 to finish with the second-highest strike rate (248.9). He backed it up with the ball too, returning 3/28 and 1/7 and making a strong case as a middle order enforcer plus allround option.RINKU ANNOUNCES PRESENCE: A batting force at the death with his sinewy power, Rinku also impressed as a safe, underrated fielder who can cover vast swathes of ground in the deep.BOWLING BLUEPRINT : India’s T20 World Cup template appears settled. Moving away from three spinners, the frontline attack features Jasprit Bumrah, Varun Chakravarthy, Arshdeep Singh and Axar Patel, with allrounders Hardik Pandya and Dube as support. Harshit Rana and Kuldeep Yadav remain second choice, likely to feature only when rotation comes into play."}

{"id": "c26aec77-f9ff-4ecf-be1e-d28bebd393f9", "title": "WhatsApp privacy policy challenged in Delhi High Court: 5 things to know", "url": "http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tech/slideshows/WhatsApp-privacy-policy-challenged-in-Delhi-High-Court-5-things-to-know/itslideshow/54332813.cms", "category": "technology", "source": "Times of India", "published_at": "2016-09-15T09:30:14+05:30", "full_text": "WhatsApp had started out with an emphatic focus on never having any ads ever on its app. But after Facebook bought it in February 2014, change appeared to be inevitable. This August, they announced updates to their privacy policy.



